	(text "Issues:\n#1 - [NEEDS CORRECTION] Add firmware test points for ARM and GPIF debugging - done, TP on SPI MISO and MOSI\n#2 - Add configurable clock test port for Si clock issue diagnostics / alternative Fs clock input - done\n#3 - EEPROM - done\n#4 -?\n#5 - ID pins, done\n#6 - USB2, USB3 resistors need to be 1% precision values -- probably not needed but done\n#7-?\n#8 - [CRITICAL] AVDD (A7) is miswired to 3.3, must be 1.2V - done\n#9 - [IMPROVEMENT] PMODE resistors should allow for both UP/DOWN/Hi-Z options, if doing SPI FLASH boot - done\n#10 - Missing recommended bulk capacitance and ferrites for *VDDQ supplies - done, ferrites were there, added 22uF caps\n#11 - [OPTIONAL] Missing series resistors on GPIF data/clock between ADC and FX3 - done, also clk\n#12 - Oscillator input should be handled as such [FSLC and CLK/XTAL inputs] - done\n#13 - SHDN should be driven by FX3 (GPIO 28) = done\n-------------\n#14 - CVDDQ voltage must match Oscillator Voltage - done, moved to +3.3V\n#15 - FX3 GPIO48, GPIO49 need TP for alt-UART use - done, using small testpoint pads\n#16 - LTC2208 SHDN should be pulled up to VDD (47k should be fine) - done\n#17 - ID5 (GPIO52) conflicts with pin mapping with in SPI boot mode - done, moved ID5 to GPIO41\n#18 - [FEATURE] 0.1\" header for JTAG pins from FX3 - done, using 2x5 0.05\" footprint\n#19 - [FEATURE] circuit to power cycle the Si5351A - done, driven by GPIO[34] \n \n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 425.45 137.16 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.1588)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "4c3169c2-a7ad-4ad0-9512-cf9b130191b2")
	)
